This article is a transcript of President Joe Biden's eulogy for Madeleine Albright, the former Secretary of State, at Washington National Cathedral. President Biden praised Albright for her dedication to freedom and her role in shaping history. He highlighted her achievements as the first female Secretary of State and her efforts to strengthen NATO and promote democracy around the world. Biden also mentioned her work as a mentor and advocate for women in national security. He emphasized the personal connection Albright had with people and her deep love for her family. The President concluded by honoring Albright's commitment to America and her belief in the power of American values.